# Engine package (`@osrs-surfing/engine`)

## Architecture

- **Pure simulation** — no DOM, Pixi, or renderer imports in `packages/engine`.
- **Snapshots** — client consumes `SimulationSnapshot` from `simulation.ts`; keep render concerns out of engine.
- **Monorepo** — client depends on engine; engine must not depend on client.

## World / tide modules

| Module | Role |
| ------ | ---- |
| `world/features.ts` | Trick zones, tide state, alpha, submersion |
| `world/trickZonePlacement.ts` | Spawn, sync, slot angles |
| `world/maps.ts` | `createCoralParkSlice` arena |
| `world/coralParkCoast.ts` | Organic reef radii |
| `game/simulation.ts` | Tick loop, tide advance, trick sync |

## Conventions

- Export constants for magic numbers (tide arcs, gaps, fade progress).
- Phase math uses `normalizeAngle`, `phaseInProgressRange`, `progressInPhaseRange` — handle wrap at 2π.
- Use conventional commit messages; run `pnpm validate` before finishing.
